      "description": "This folder contains high-level smoke validation checks to confirm that core API endpoints are reachable and responding correctly. These tests verify service availability, basic response integrity, and acceptable response times. Smoke tests are intended to provide rapid feedback in CI pipelines and act as the first indicator of system health."
    },
    {
      "name": "02 - Functional Tests",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Post 1 (Functional Validation)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Correct post ID returned\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.id).to.eql(1);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Post has required fields\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property(\"userId\");\r",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property(\"title\");\r",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property(\"body\");\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Title is not empty\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.title.length).to.be.greaterThan(0);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "const schema = {\r",
                  "    type: \"object\",\r",
                  "    required: [\"userId\", \"id\", \"title\", \"body\"],\r",
                  "    properties: {\r",
                  "        userId: { type: \"number\" },\r",
                  "        id: { type: \"number\" },\r",
                  "        title: { type: \"string\" },\r",
                  "        body: { type: \"string\" }\r",
                  "    }\r",
                  "};\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Response matches JSON schema\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.jsonSchema(schema);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  ""
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/posts/1",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "posts",
                "1"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "This folder contains functional validation tests focused on response correctness and data integrity. These checks verify that API responses contain expected fields, correct identifiers, and valid content structures. Functional tests ensure that business logic and data contracts are behaving as intended beyond simple availability checks."
    },
    {
      "name": "03 - Negative Tests",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Invalid Post (Negative Test)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Request handled without crashing\", function () {\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Response structure is safe\", function () {\r",
                  "    let data;\r",
                  "    try {\r",
                  "        data = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "    } catch (e) {\r",
                  "        data = null;\r",
                  "    }\r",
                  "    pm.expect(data === null || typeof data === \"object\").to.be.true;\r",
                  "});\r",
                  "\r",
                  "pm.test(\"Response time under threshold\", function () {\r",
                  "    const limit = Number(pm.environment.get(\"timeout_limit\")) || 500;\r",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(limit);\r",
                  "});\r",
                  ""
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/posts/999999",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "posts",
                "999999"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "This folder contains error-handling and resilience tests designed to validate how the API responds to invalid or unexpected inputs. These scenarios ensure the system handles failure conditions safely, returns appropriate status codes, and maintains stability under adverse conditions. Negative testing is critical for assessing system robustness."
    },
